cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DS 

The paper discusses optimization problems in high dimensional spaces, which is a common topic in machine learning and neural network research. The focus on saddle points and their impact on optimization suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are the most likely sub-categories. The use of statistical physics and random matrix theory suggests a possible connection to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the application of the proposed algorithm to deep or recurrent neural network training suggests a possible connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
